 mature the team will be at a given point in time, which raises questions about whether the forecasting is accurate. The team leader asks everyone to review the page and update it if necessary.\n\n   The team also discusses a fiscal year down, stays level trends, and how it can be seen in the charts. The team leader thanks Josh for creating the page and encourages everyone to check it out.\n\n   TEAM UPDATES\n   The team leader provides some updates on new hires, including Gabe Weaver, who will be leading a third manage PM team. The team leader also mentions that Dove has been hired as an APM monitoring, and thanks everyone who was involved in the hiring process.\n\n   LANGUAGE CHANGES\n   The team discusses some language changes that were made to the handbook, specifically around customer results. The team leader explains that the changes were made to emphasize the importance of customer feedback, but also to ensure that internal feedback is not prioritized over external feedback.\n\n   CUSTOMER TRAINING\n   The team leader mentions that customer training discovery training will be coming soon, led by Sarah O''Donnell and her team. The training will include quick videos on various customer discovery topics, which will be embedded in the how we work description on the team page.\n\n   FEEDBACK AND NEXT STEPS\n   The team leader thanks Josh for leading the 12, two kick off feedback session and provides some feedback on the session. The team discusses the importance of having screenshots and mock-ups for front-end work and how it can help with the customer discovery flow.\n\n   The team leader encourages everyone to prioritize and do what matters most first, and to seek external feedback in addition to internal feedback. The meeting ends with a discussion on the next steps and action items for the team.\n\n   ACTION ITEMS\n   The team has several action items, including reviewing the category maturity page, updating the page if necessary, and following up on customer contacts. The team leader also asks everyone to prioritize and do what matters most first, and to seek external feedback in addition to internal feedback.\n\n   CONCLUSION\n   In conclusion, the team meeting covered a range of topics, including reminders, technical discussions, team updates, language changes, customer training, and feedback. The team leader encouraged everyone to prioritize and do what matters most first, and to seek external feedback in addition to internal feedback. The meeting ended with a discussion on the next steps and action items for the team.', 'Team Meeting', 'completed', '[{\"timestamp\":\"02:40\",\"text\":\"[Visual Context at 02:40]\",\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\Ashin\\\\AppData\\\\Local\\\\Temp\\\\SummarAI\\\\visuals\\\\vid_1769768734\\\\slide_02_40.jpg\",\"ocr_status\":\"Permission Denied\"},{\"timestamp\":\"05:20\",\"text\":\"[Visual Context at 05:20]\",\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\Ashin\\\\AppData\\\\Local\\\\Temp\\\\SummarAI\\\\visuals\\\\vid_1769768734\\\\slide_05_20.jpg\",\"ocr_status\":\"Permission Denied\"},{\"timestamp\":\"08:00\",\"text\":\"[Visual Context at 08:00]\",\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\Ashin\\\\AppData\\\\Local\\\\Temp\\\\SummarAI\\\\visuals\\\\vid_1769768734\\\\slide_08_00.jpg\",\"ocr_status\":\"Permission Denied\"},{\"timestamp\":\"10:40\",\"text\":\"[Visual Context at 10:40]\",\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\Ashin\\\\AppData\\\\Local\\\\Temp\\\\SummarAI\\\\visuals\\\\vid_1769768734\\\\slide_10_40.jpg\",\"ocr_status\":\"Permission Denied\"},{\"timestamp\":\"13:20\",\"text\":\"[Visual Context at 13:20]\",\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\Ashin\\\\AppData\\\\Local\\\\Temp\\\\SummarAI\\\\visuals\\\\vid_1769768734\\\\slide_13_20.jpg\",\"ocr_status\":\"Permission Denied\"},{\"timestamp\":\"16:01\",\"text\":\"[Visual Context at 16:01]\",\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\Ashin\\\\AppData\\\\Local\\\\Temp\\\\SummarAI\\\\visuals\\\\vid_1769768734\\\\slide_16_01.jpg\",\"ocr_status\":\"Permission Denied\"},{\"timestamp\":\"18:41\",\"text\":\"[Visual Cont