ung susulod pala. So baga di rin makatarungan. And I will give activity ano. So your activity will be posted later on. So can you refer na lang to your Google Classroom for your activity in this subject. Okay, how about the others? Can they open your camera? Okay. In a count of 1, 2, 3. Okay. That will be all lang muna, guys. Thank you and goodbye. and good afternoon. Thank you, sir. Thank you.', 'INTRODUCTION TO SOCIAL ADVOCACY\nThe concept of social advocacy was introduced, and students were asked to share their ideas about it. Social advocacy is about promoting social change, as noted by one of the students. It involves advancing the interests of social justice, particularly on behalf of populations or groups that have been disadvantaged, disempowered, or discriminated against.\n\nDEFINITIONS OF SOCIAL ADVOCACY\nThree definitions of social advocacy were discussed. The first definition states that social advocacy is to advance the interests of social justice, particularly on behalf of populations or groups that have been disadvantaged, disempowered, or discriminated against. This includes helping those who are being discriminated against due to their disabilities. The second definition explains that social advocacy is about helping individuals to speak up for themselves, ensuring that their views and opinions are heard and understood. The third definition highlights that social advocacy involves supporting individuals to speak up or speaking on their behalf to help them get what they are entitled to.\n\nTYPES OF ADVOCACY\nThere are different types of advocacy, including individual advocacy, citizen advocacy, and systems advocacy. Individual advocacy focuses on one or two people and can be informal or formal. Informal individual advocacy involves family members, friends, or relatives taking on advocacy roles, while formal individual advocacy involves paid staff advocating for individuals. Citizen advocacy is a community-based movement that aims to recognize, promote, and defend the rights, well-being, and interests of people with intellectual and multiple disabilities. Systems advocacy is primarily concerned with influencing and changing the system, such as legislation or policy and practices, to benefit people with disabilities as a group within society.\n\nIMPORTANCE OF SOCIAL ADVOCACY\nSocial advocacy is essential for promoting social justice and supporting individuals who are disadvantaged, disempowered, or discriminated against. It helps to ensure that their views and opinions are heard and understood, and that they receive the support and services they need. Social advocacy also plays a crucial role in changing the system to make it more inclusive and equitable for all.\n\nCONCLUSION\nIn conclusion, social advocacy is a vital concept that involves promoting social change and advancing the interests of social justice. It includes various types of advocacy, such as individual, citizen, and systems advocacy, each with its unique focus and goals. By understanding the definitions and types of social advocacy, individuals can better appreciate the importance of promoting social justice and supporting those who are disadvantaged, disempowered, or discriminated against.', 'Educational', 'completed', '[{\"timestamp\":\"02:59\",\"text\":\"[Visual Context at 02:59]\",\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\Ashin\\\\AppData\\\\Local\\\\Temp\\\\SummarAI\\\\visuals\\\\vid_1770006126\\\\slide_02_59.jpg\",\"ocr_status\":\"Permission Denied\"},{\"timestamp\":\"05:59\",\"text\":\"[Visual Context at 05:59]\",\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\Ashin\\\\AppData\\\\Local\\\\Temp\\\\SummarAI\\\\visuals\\\\vid_1770006126\\\\slide_05_59.jpg\",\"ocr_status\":\"Permission Denied\"},{\"timestamp\":\"08:58\",\"text\":\"[Visual Context at 08:58]\",\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\Ashin\\\\AppData\\\\Local\\\\Temp\\\\SummarAI\\\\visuals\\\\vid_1770006126\\\\slide_08_58.jpg\",\"ocr_status\":\"Permission Denied\"},{\"timestamp\":\"11:58\",\"text\":\"[Visual Context at 11:58]\",\"pa